";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5607:"<p>Today I had a great meeting with Michael Kalina (@<a href="http://twitter.com/mkalina" target="_blank">mkalina</a> on twitter) who is specialized in building high-quality WordPress themes. He gave me quite useful feedback for my plugin which I decided to implement with v2.9.1.</p>
<p>One personal request: as WordPress added a new review feature for plugins hosted on wordpress.org, I kindly invite you to leave your opinion about my plugin at <a href="http://wordpress.org/support/view/plugin-reviews/leaflet-maps-marker" target="_blank">http://wordpress.org/support/view/plugin-reviews/leaflet-maps-marker</a>.</p>
<p>Here´s what´s new in detail in v2.9.1:</p>
<p><strong>improved backend usability</strong></p>
<p>The form fields for marker and layer shortcode now automatically focus if you select them:</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1623" title="shortcode" src="http://cdn.mapsmarker.com/wp-content/uploads/shortcode.png" alt="" width="551" height="46" /></p>
<p>This makes it easier to copy the shortcode and paste it into a post or page.</p>
<p><strong>refreshed backend design</strong></p>
<p>I minimized the admin header and button now turn dark blue when you are on the selected page:</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1624" title="header" src="http://cdn.mapsmarker.com/wp-content/uploads/header.png" alt="" width="909" height="116" /></p>
<p>The former header moved into the new footer on each page.</p>
<p>I also did some finetuning on tables (no more header with columns &#8220;Parameter&#8221; and &#8220;Value&#8221;, maximized their widths etc) and headings.</p>
<p><strong>Translations updates</strong></p>
<p>Thanks to many motivated contributors, v2.9.1 comes with the following translation updates:</p>
<p>Updated translations</p>
<ul>
<li>Spanish translation thanks to Alvaro Lara, <a href="http://www.alvarolara.com" target="_blank">http://www.alvarolara.com</a></li>
<li>Chinese translation thanks to John Shen, <a href="http://www.synyan.net" target="_blank">http://www.synyan.net</a></li>
<li>Catalan translation thanks to Vicent Cubells, <a href="http://vcubells.net" target="_blank">http://vcubells.net</a></li>
<li>Polish translation thanks to Tomasz Rudnicki, <a href="http://www.kochambieszczady.pl" target="_blank">http://www.kochambieszczady.pl</a></li>
<li>Dutch translation thanks to Patrick Ruers, <a href="http://www.stationskwartiersittard.nl" target="_blank">http://www.stationskwartiersittard.nl</a></li>
<li>German translation</li>
</ul>
<p>If you want to contribute to translations, please visit <a href="http://translate.mapsmarker.com/projects/lmm" target="_blank">http://translate.mapsmarker.com/projects/lmm</a> for more information.</p>
<p><strong>Outlook &#8211; my plans for the next release<br />
</strong></p>
<p>I am currently working hard on preparing a pro version with even more features like adding markers from frontend, marker clustering, gpx support and more. More details about this version will follow soon.</p>
<p><strong>Full changelog </strong>(<a title="Releases / Changelog" href="http://www.mapsmarker.com/docs/changelog/">show previous changelogs</a>)<strong><br />
</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>CHANGED: improved backend usability</li>
<li>CHANGED: refreshed backend design</li>
<li>CHANGED: updated Chinese translation thanks to John Shen, <a href="http://www.synyan.net" target="_blank">http://www.synyan.net</a></li>
<li>CHANGED: updated Catalan translation thanks to Vicent Cubells, <a href="http://vcubells.net" target="_blank">http://vcubells.net</a></li>
<li>CHANGED: updated Polish translation thanks to Tomasz Rudnicki, <a href="http://www.kochambieszczady.pl" target="_blank">http://www.kochambieszczady.pl</a></li>
<li>CHANGED: updated Dutch translation thanks to Patrick Ruers, <a href="http://www.stationskwartiersittard.nl" target="_blank">http://www.stationskwartiersittard.nl</a></li>
<li>CHANGED: updated German translation</li>
</ul>
<p>Please let me what you think of this new release. If you have any issues, please see <a href="http://www.mapsmarker.com/support/">this page</a> on how to get support. If an important feature is missing, please add your feature requests <a title="Ideas" href="http://www.mapsmarker.com/ideas/">on Github</a>. I am also looking for more translations &#8211; if you would like to contribute a new one, please visit <a title="Languages" href="http://www.mapsmarker.com/languages/">this page</a> for more information. And of course I´d very appreciate your review for my plugin on <a href="http://wordpress.org/support/view/plugin-reviews/leaflet-maps-marker" target="_blank">wordpress.org</a> <img src='http://cdn.mapsmarker.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif' alt=';-)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
